# E2E Test Code Review

When the user asks to **review the newly added tests** or similar (e.g. "review test changes", "code review my tests"):

## 1. Identify files to review

Run `git status` and `git diff --name-only` to find **newly added or modified files** under:
- `tests/cucumber/features/` (`.feature`)
- `tests/cucumber/steps/` (`.ts`)
- `tests/cucumber/support/` (`.ts` — pages, utilities, world, config)

Include only test-related files. Ignore unrelated changes.

## 2. Load the checklist

Read `docs/CODE_REVIEW.md` fully. Use its checklist as the review standard.

## 3. Review each file

For each identified file:
- Read the file contents
- Check against every applicable checklist item (e.g. feature files → section 1; steps → section 2; page objects → section 3)
- Note pass (✅) or violation (❌) with file path and line number

## 4. Report

Use the output format from CODE_REVIEW.md:
- For each violation: **File**, **Line(s)**, **Check**, **Issue**, **Fix**
- Summary: X passed, Y failed
- List all violations with concrete suggested fixes

Be precise. Cite line numbers and quote the offending code. Provide copy-pasteable fixes when possible.
